						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 958, Dhātu, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1036 December 24 Friday.</hi> The date is not verifiable. The record refers itself to the reign of the Chālukya king <hi rend="bold">Jagadēka[malladēva]</hi> (Jayasiṁha II) and records the gift of some land to <hi rend="bold">Mādhava-Shaḍaṅgi</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇayya</hi> for having immersed the bones of <hi rend="bold">Noḷaṁbamahādēvī</hi> in the Ganges. Mentions <hi rend="bold">Dēvaladēvī,</hi> the king's wife and the daughter of Noḷaṁba, and the Noḻaṁba feudatory <hi rend="bold">[Uda]yādityadēva.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
